<div id="review_1388909565" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1388909565" />
    <a title="Rick Slane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17459218-rick-slane"><img alt="Rick Slane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552977455p2/17459218.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1388909565?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rick Slane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rick Slane" href="/user/show/17459218-rick-slane">Rick Slane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="cloth 9780394432625" href="/book/show/977345.Kristin_Lavransdatter">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Men who want to understand traditional women a little more</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17459218-rick-slane?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17459218-rick-slane?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17459218-rick-slane?shelf=impressive">impressive</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17459218-rick-slane?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17459218-rick-slane?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1388909565" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11343257082668242973"><p>I read the &quot;unauthentic archaic language&quot; original translation by Charles Archer that is &quot;not true to...original Norwegian text&quot; according to Ashley&apos;s review and I did almost give up after 20 or 40 pages but I kept going anyway. It&apos;s so good now I&apos;m tracking down the Nunnally translation.</p> <p> This work is very Catholic and traditional in its examination of morality. It is written from a woman&apos;s point of view and this makes for much of the trilogy&apos;s uniqueness. Her father arranges her a secure marri</p></span>
  <span id="freeText11343257082668242973" style="display:none"><p>I read the "unauthentic archaic language" original translation by Charles Archer that is "not true to...original Norwegian text" according to Ashley's review and I did almost give up after 20 or 40 pages but I kept going anyway. It's so good now I'm tracking down the Nunnally translation.</p> <p> This work is very Catholic and traditional in its examination of morality. It is written from a woman's point of view and this makes for much of the trilogy's uniqueness. Her father arranges her a secure marriage but she falls in love with a carefree noble adventurer. The action take place in 1300-1350 Norway.</p><p>OK I've read the other translation and recommend it instead. It's modern &amp; easier to read. The old translation was artificially archaic. I will post a review at that edition.</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="11343257082668242973" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


